text: Toole County is a county in the northern U.S. state of Montana. As of the 2020 United States Census, 4,971 people lived there. Its county seat is Shelby. The county was created in 1914 from parts of Hill County and Teton County and was named after Joseph Toole, the first and fourth governor of Montana.
